caption: Fantastic place, chicken sandwich was great, and the passion fruit ice tea was amazing. I even got a free dessert with a coupon. 10/10
Have to say this is awesome chicken!

Holy hot chicken!! Ordered both a medium and an extra hot sandwich and definitely wasn't disappointed! Great heat but also great flavor, awesome curly fries and quartered chicken also. Definitely check out this colorful and unique place if you're looking for something different with a great expansive menu. Can't wait to return!
I think 5 stars says enough... P.s. If you have the Munchies this is Da spottt

It was delicious. I got the medium spicy ("Hot") chicken sandwich and fries. The spice level was good - made my nose run a bit, but was very manageable. I think I'll try the x-hot next time. The chicken breast was huge, and moist. One order of fries was more than enough to share - they were hot and crispy, a combination of curly and waffle fries. Indoor dining is closed right now. They have up a big plexiglass divider between customers and the cashier. No one else was there while I ordered and waited for my food to be ready.
Hands down best Hot fried chicken sandwich in the city! It’s massive and crazy amount of flavor! If you like spice, they def have you covered! The graffiti in the building is dope too!

The crispy fried chicken (no sauce ) was amazing on many levels .  The big boss chicken sandwich with the big boss sauce .. was O soo good.. This is going to be my go to fry chicken place. When driving through the city..

Big Boss is my go-to local chicken spot. Their chicken is so good and spicy, they even take care to package it for delivery, like the popcorn chicken and sweet potato fries boxes were left open so they don't get soggy during the transport.
3rd time going and all 3 times their spicy chicken sandwich has been worth it.
If you decide to order. Please expect it to be cold.
Delicious chicken 🤤🔥
spicy teriyaki chicken is great. the spicy chicken soup is pure habanero but I liked it.
First experience today, really good food and super juicy. A lot of stuff not available cause of COVID, so hopefully get to try it next time

We were so excited to try out this local restaurant but things took a turn. We got food poisoning. After eating half way through the second piece, I noticed that the chicken breast were undercooked. Now, we are suffering the consequences.
Love it
The medium spicy says” feel the burn”, and it’s true! Not only when you eat it, but also the next day. It’s delicious and has good price, I’m just not prepared for the spicy.

Their spicy fried chicken ain't no joke at all. They have four levels of spiciness to choose from. I chose two which were Medium & Hot. That Medium fried chicken sandwich had a kick of a little hotness to it. I let one of my coworkers have the Hot fried Chicken sandwich. Now the rest of the team wants chicken sandwiches now. I called Big Boss for my coworkers but we're too far for BB in-house deliveries. Fortunately they also have contract deliveries(Door Dash, Post Mates, & Uber Eats) for spots outside their in-house delivery borders.

After my first visit here a year ago, I came back to try the same meals again. I am very impressed with the change they made in the food, as it seems the owners listened to the feedback and reviews!  This time, the chicken are battered perfectly with the same taste & improved presentation! I love the flavor of the hot sauce (supposed to Nashville hot chicken style?) , but fair warning that it can be very spicy. The chicken sandwich is still big as ever and the hot sauce is fire. The chicken and sandiches are worth the prices (~$8-$13). They also expanded their menu to onclude more combos and other sides. I am really happy to see that the locally owned chicken business is still around, and made great improvements.
Really spicy chicken sandwich
Great crispy chicken joint. Chicken sandwich was big. Enough for 2 people.

Honestly, my favorite things here is not even the fried chicken, athough the chicken is really good. I have had the spicy chicken sandwich (third level which was extremely spicy even for a spicy-ophile like me), sauced, and no sauce chicken (my favorite). My favorite two things to have here are the fries and coleslaw. I've come here a handful of times now, and everything has always been consistently good.
They should mention that their chicken sandwiches are made using thighs. I hate thigh meat. I didn't notice this until I got home and had to throw it in the garbage.

There was no effort to actually contain the chicken in the sandwich; it extended twice the width of the bun. I feel sick after eating it. The fries were not crispy. I will not go here again. I honestly would rather get Popeyes.
My Slot ✊🏾✊🏾✊🏾
Very rude and impatient staffs.
The best and definitely one of a kind spicy chicken sandwich!!!
Best item fried sweet potatoes yummy and different.   The chicken was good, I will go back.
Chicken was spicy, chicken wasn’t all that fresh though. I’ll probably pass on a repeat.

I love the Big Boss Chicken Sandwich. I've been going almost every week for the past few months now. As I begin to give my information they cut me off and say "Jerry, what you want?"(in a friendly way.) Lol I like that. The flavors are delicious and their extreme is hot af. I love spicy food. Worth the money and its only a 10 minute wait. A mask is required for pickup.

I came across Big Boss Spicy Chicken while watching a segment of Chicago's best. I think from there I built a high expectation as the huge foodie I am. Considering I have tried numerous Chicken joints all over the city, including suburbs. After a couple weeks of reading the reviews and talking about it with my co worker, we decided to order it for pick up.  We ordered the big boss spicy chicken sandwich (medium heat) and an order of Curly Fries.  As I arrived there were at least 4 people waiting on their order, I had placed it over the phone. After they said 10 minutes, I took at least 15 min to make sure it was ready once I arrived. When I got there, I couldn't find any parking as it was on a busy street and had very limited parking space. I ended up parking across where there was a gas station. When I arrived I had to wait another 6 min as they were behind. Order ended up taking at least 20 minutes.  First good thing: The fries were crispy and pretty tasty. I almost finished the box of fries (pretty big- could be shared) before I even took a bite of the sandwich. Let down: The chicken sandwich did not live up to the expectations. Wasn't crispy enough although it was fried, the sauce was tasty but not as spicy as some reviews mentioned the medium sauce to be. The chicken did not seem the best quality, I dislike the brown spots and slim/skin in between bites. I cut it in half to try to finish it but only ate half, but not because it was amazing.  Although I support all business, I'm not 100% I would go back to try the other Items.
Very hot
Pretty mediocre, should of saved my $19 🤷🏾‍♂️
Combo way worth the price. Chicken well spiced
Their chicken sandwich is so good! Nothing quite like it in Chicago. If you like extremely spicy foods, this is the place to be!
Big boss spicy chicken sandwich is phenomenal!!

Delicious is the only word I can use for this place! Their spicy fried chicken sandwich was delicious. I recommend getting the mild spicy fried chicken sandwich with the pickle salad and curly cheese fries. We got takeout and I highly recommend coming here!

I had the Big Boss Chicken sandwich and it was honestly underwhelming, it was more sweet than spicy and it gave me a headache to remember. The quantity of food you get for $8 though is amazing, so it was well worth the money. The chicken sandwich to me is amazing in quantity, but is lacking in spice. Also I didn’t like the art of their restaurant , but that’s just my opinion and got nothing to do with the food.

Good quantity and good taste. We ordered the half bird and the spicy sandwich both on medium heat. Although the quantity and taste were great, I felt that one of the pieces of the bird had a peculiar odor. And the meal did not react too well with my stomach. I'm thinking it might have been just that one piece.
Great Chicken

Was not a fan. None of them were wearing masks behind the counter (despite having a sign saying it was mandatory), and the chicken was chewy and not great. They also got my friend's order wrong and weren't happy about having to remake it.
Delicious 😋
I got the mild chicken sandwich it’s pretty good but next time ima try the sauce lol the lady who took my order was pretty rude tho

After viewing the episode of Chicago's Best, where Big Boss Chicken was featured, the decision was made....It was raining, the streets were flooding, but we still had to make a trip to the city to try out the BIG BOSS spicy chicken sandwich. My husband and I both ordered the Big Boss, mine was mild, his was hot. The chicken was fried perfectly, with the right amount of seasoning. For it to be such a gloomy day, the building was radiant, bright and catches your eye. We will definitely be back!!
Awful service, taste is better than I thought

Quality and quantity. $8 for basically a foot long of chicken in this sandwich. The cheese and jalepeno are key!! WARNING THOUGH: Their fried jalepenos are not batter fried, they’re whole jalepenos fried in oil- still delicious but SO SO SPICY.
They truly know the meaning of spicy
The Chicken Sandwich, mac &cheese, fries, & passion fruit tea are the reason I drive miles to this place..Soooo Bomb...

Love love love the food here! It's amazing! I gave 4 stars because every time I've gone, my order was messed up in some way. But still, I think the food is well worth it! Just be sure to check inside your bag to make sure you got everything you ordered before you leave the restaurant!
Very delicious chicken and very reasonable price wise. Get the sweet potatoes and pickle salad also. Currently have clear dividers up and I felt safe picking up.
If your into spicy chicken sandwiches. I highly suggest the BIG BOSS HOT SANDWICH!! ITS FIRE BUT GOOD!!!
BEST SPICY FRIED CHICKEN PERIOD
Nice atmosphere
Good, great.

Tried Big Boss via Uber eats. My food was hot and the flavor was great just right spice without sauce but the wings are just too big for me. Next time I will see if they have party wings. If you like huge wings then this is definitely the place for you. 👍🏾 good wings though
Very spicy chicken and delicious! You can also have the spicy sauce on the side.
it's aight to much hype on Chicago best
Best fries in the city
They have The BEST spicy chicken sandwich in Chicago, all the food here is always hot fresh and cooked to order - visit one time and you'll be hooked!
IT WAS EVERYTHING!!!!!!!! SO DELICIOUS!!!!😋😋😋😋
Spicy but good food
Excellent flavor. Super spicy chicken.

I didn't like it. I had read all these amazing reviews, and it's pretty close by, so I gave it a try with my partner. When we walked in, it was empty, but a woman was at the counter. She took our orders, and then she disappeared until it was ready. My first bite was great! I thought it was gonna all be great. The piece of chicken was huge, so my first bite was just the edge of the chicken. As I got to the sandwiches part, i realized the slaw was too oniony for me and I eventually removed the slaw. My partner got to the center and said he couldn't go on, because it started to taste and smell fishy. I thought nothing of it until I got to the center of mine, and mine also tasted fishy, so I pulled the chicken apart and the center was a big fatty pocket that wreaked like fish! I couldn't eat anymore either. I was grossed out by it in the end. I don't know if the fryer isn't being cleaned or changed like it should or if the oil was bad or the chicken was old, but since it wasn't just mine and a few other reviewers mention it too, I wouldn't recommend it.

Unfortunately i was unable to try the chicken, I came last night but i forgot my wallet. I had my girlfriend send me a picture of my bank card and my liscense. I understand they want to protect against fraud but I had a receipt with my name and the last digits of my card, my car insurance with my name and address, my vehicle registration with my name and address and a letter with my name and address. Yet they still refused to accept the payment. I feel that was quite unreasonable considering how much information i had to prove it was my card.

I had the big boss chicken sandwich,  I didn't have sauce (ok I was scared) but it was mildly spicy and tolerable. It was crispy yet flavorful, it was almost like extra meat. The waffle fries were seasoned just right. I also had the jumbo wings they were also good. I will definitely be returning, and don't forget the passion fruit tea, very tasty. The decor adds a nice touch!

The chicken sandwich is tasty, especially the coleslaw. Loved the curly fries! My only issue was the bathroom. It was dirty (toilet seat covered in urine), the seat was loose and the soap was watery. I would eat there again but probably get take out.

My office and I have ordered this place 2 times now on grub hub; both times it was absolutely amazing. The order was correct both times. The chicken is huge, tender, crispy, and juicy! We also got free French toast because our order was over 30$ and wow what a treat! Our new favorite place. Thank you!
Good food

Tried the spicy chicken sandwich the spicy level was "hot" wasnt hot at all in my opinion. Was pretty disappointed in the quality of the meat it felt slimy and felt sick afterwards my boyfriend had to pull over on our way home to throw up which he never does. The fried sweet potato was really good, but that's all we really enjoyed.
Not the warmest atmosphere or gentlest customer service, but the chicken sandwich came out quickly and was hot, super-crispy, perfectly spiced, and one of the best I've eaten.
Omg... it hit the spot!!! Very good!!!

I ordered a sandwich, 2 tenders, and some curry puffs. They were all very good, the portions for the tenders were quite big despite just being 4 pieces. I'd say one order is enough for two people. The sandwich itself consisted of a very large chicken patty, way bigger than the bun itself, which is appreciated, and the curry puffs are kind of a mix between a somosa and a crab Ragoon. I'll definitely be back!
worth the drove from o'hare. delicious spicy fried chicken

I truly have nothing positive to say about this experience. We went to try the chicken sandwich and went ahead and threw in some cheese fries. The meat on the chicken sandwich was slimy it felt disgusting to eat, I couldn’t even get through half of it. My husband and I came home both wanting to throw it up. The fries are the type that come frozen, so nothing positive to say there either. Not to mention the lady at the register is not exactly the most pleasant. Popeyes or Chick-fil-A is honestly better and not to mention cheaper and likely better quality.

Friends has been recommending to this place for months, after getting disappointed from Popeyes chicken sandwich for having lack of flavor and dryness. This place is a hidden gem at Bridgeport, decent price and a giant portion of a chicken sandwich. I don’t think I ever had a chicken sandwich as tender as this, the popcorn chicken was good, the teriyaki thigh not so much. For only $1 getting a large portion chicken thigh and the soup was creamy and filling.
Food waa amazing.  Location is small
Very tasty. Highly recommend trying the tenders and the fries. My wife loves the sweet potato "fries"
Excellent chicken sandwich. Nice and hot, very large piece of chicken, and tasty toppings. A small venue, but it works.
Hell yea, spicy chicken sandwich with a real home sauce. Fire.

Excellent chicken sandwich. Extremely spicy so watch the spice level when ordering.  Has a very unique flavor not found in other chicken sandwiches. Popeye's a few months ago had the best Chicken sandwich,but then it was discontinued and the chicken sandwich that came back now is not as good as before. Big Boss Chicken is the new standard and they sell cheese for the sandwich, Popeye's does not. Taste and be amazed.

Not exactly the best chicken sandwich. However, it will definitely fill you up. It's a little bit on the greasy side. I think their potato wedges were pretty good and their lemonade was very tasty. In my opinion, I don't think this particular place would hold up with other fast food restaurants like Popeye's or Chick-fil-A. Although, this place is just OK!
Spicy and delicious. Would suggest allowing patrons to use tap water if possible
Great sandwich in the big boss! Also the chicken was great.
They served me spoiled Chicken, would not recommend this place.
THE SERVICE COULD BE BETTER.
Food  wasn't  that good for the  price
Yes this chicken is so good.

Willing to pay a bit extra than Popeyes for a HUGE chicken sandwich with lots of flavor all while avoiding a 30 minute wait and potential fistfight?? Check this place out! The chicken is a huge portion. You can basically make a whole 2nd sandwich out of it. The fries are also really good!

Cool little hip place with a graffitied type decor. I ordered the bigboss spicy but apparently they have hidden levels that are even spicier so i ended up asking for the spiciest level they have. Im a spice freak so the hotter the better and let me say, this sandwich did not disappoint. Although the level of spice i chose might be unbearable for most, for the spice lovers, the sandwich still managed to have great overall taste without having the spice take over the entire sandwich. Definitely going to be a repeat customer whenever i need a spicy chicken sandwich fill, and also the portion size is enourmous.

Amazing food the chicken sandwich is a most . And the fried sweet potato’s are amazing too. Wish they had some sore of honey sauce for them but they’re pretty great by themselves too. The portions are big and the place have such an urban vibe . If you ever find yourself around here definaly recome y stopping for some great food .

Definitely do not recommend. I ordered their chicken sandwich, their spicy flavor “hot” is pretty okay it’s not really spicy but the chicken it’s self it more breaded than actual chicken. Once you take a  bite of the chicken it doesn’t look so fresh nor appealing. Their waffle fries are crispy but a little greasy. Plus, it was a little expensive for ordering 2 chicken sandwiches 2 waffle fries and sodas for $30. Not including tip.
This is amazing

Extremely good, I really enjoyed the big boss sandwich. The chicken was juicy and flavorful. Added a leg & thigh for $1 the regular chicken was great, nice flavorful kick, tiny bit of spice. The spot is cool, it's small, but can accommodate about 16 people to eat in at a time. Food is cooked fresh to order and took about 10 minutes to have our meal brought out. This place is great, please support them.
Boss Spicy LvL3 accomplsihed
Pretty good and it's actully quite filling
Delicious i got delivery and it was perfect end to my wife and my day. Will repeat again.  French toast, just add it always
Amazing fried chicken and the sauces are to die for!

The fried chicken sandwich is huge, it's a perfect chicken sandwich but not extraordinary. I got the hot but could have went hotter. Come for the sandwich and stay for the cheese fries! Think a seasoned Chik-fil-a waffle fry meets cheese and have a baby....YUM!

Southwest Chinatown has this gem of a Chicken place that does great justice to the 'spicy' in its name. Would highly recommend their signature Big Boss Sandwich to anyone who loves chicken. Beyond the 5 spice levels stated on their menu (Crispy fried, Medium, Hot, X Hot, Big Boss Hot) are 3 hidden levels of hotness. You could go all the way up to the Big Boss Hot x3 if you want to do that to yourself. The servers are very welcoming and amicable and space usually isn't an issue on weekends. They are open till 10 although Yelp and their website might show different times. Definitely coming back ♥️🐔🍗🔥
The best chicken sandwich I have ever had.

Let me start by saying the hype of this place is well over rated. It's ok but no where near great. The chicken sandwich was my least favorite,  the cole slaw is not house made, the mac and cheese was more like a soup and I couldn't make sense of what I was eating. The atmosphere felt cheap, miss matched eating utensils,  styrofoam plates and chairs at the window that felt like they were from IKEA . My chair wobbled so much I felt it was going to brake while eating. I had high hopes for this place but will not be returning. There are better options for fried chicken in the city.
Chicken was cooked perfectly! Moist.
omg the medium spicy chicken sandwich taste so good. definitely coming back again soon very soon

This place is legit. Had the hot tenders - not insanely spicy, and very well done.  Service was excellent. Will be back many many times. Side note - I’m from Nashville, and this chicken still bangs hard.
Delicious spot
Aye that PICKLE SALAD tho...
Realy good. The sweet potatoes are amazing. Small place. Not a lot of seating. Great service
I saw this place on Hungry Hound NOT what I thought it qas @ ALL!!!
Delicious chicken and the big boss spicy is not for the faint of heart!
The chicken sandwich and fried French toast were awesomely amazing!

not a good choice. very expensive for what is essentially fast food (chicken sandwich + fries = $14) and the food was just ok. I got the spiciest heat level and the heat/flavor was good but the chicken thigh was stringy and tasted refried, like they had cooked it once that morning and then again to order.  there's too much great food around in the bridgeport/chinatown/pilsen area, save the hot chicken for nashville.
Popeyes ain’t got nothing on this!
good thing the gooey breading came off the bruised thigh meat with my first bite or I wouldn't have seen the sharp bone in the next bite
Really good food love the big boss sandwich

Stop reading and just GO!!! I am a lover of Chick Fil A Spicy Chicken Sandwich and this place has outdone them!! My God the spicy flavored chicken was amazing! I've never had anything like it and I'm a foodie!  Plus the chicken was large enough for 2 sandwiches (U might want to get an extra bun!) The bun itself is delicious!  Con: We paid $6 for parking. I'll be calling in my order next time 😉

WOW. What a delicious spicy chicken sandwich!!!!! We definitely over ordered and they do not skimp. The portions are very size-able and great for sharing so you can get different things to try. We got the chicken sandwich (not spicy) the half chicken box (medium spicy), grilled cheese, corn, Mac n cheese, and cheese fries. The medium is SO SPICY I recommend lots of water when you eat this. I cannot even imagine what the fire hot spicy is.....
Chicken sandwich is great.   Spice levels seem appropriate. Passion fruit tea is great.  I didn’t enjoy the first crush though but interesting.

So delicious. I had the chicken sandwich medium sauce. Very tender and the slaw added just the right amount of sweetness. Kinda expensive, but as a treat it's worth it. Cheese fries were also delicious.

At first glance this restaurant is nothing more than a wall of graffiti, set aside to endure the harsh weathers of Chicago. But no. It’s more than that.  This restaurant is a hidden gem, and I only found out about this place through a friend. I have to say, I thought it was all jokes until I walked into the “wall of graffiti”  The chicken, which it is known for, although pricey, exhibits a juicy interior complementing its crunchy exterior. If you are a weak person of spice (as I am) go for the medium sauce. You may also find that very spicy (i found it so)  Other than the food, the restaurant interior is clean and simple, and the cashier is nice.  5/5 would come here again after I build up my spice tolerance.
The chicken was ok. Expensive! The service was sub par. The server got my order wrong and misunderstood most of what I wanted, and was quite unapologetic. I wont go back.

username: Mad Science of Chicago's Western Suburbs

caption: The food is good. I had the mild chicken sandwich which definitely had a kick to it. They use a huge piece of chicken and it was very well cooked and juicy. I shared the fries (combo of waffle and curly) which was fine as a side to the sandwich. Was not a huge fan of the Mac and cheese, it was soggy and overpriced and wasn't anything special. I deducted a star bc the bathroom could be cleaner and they use styrofoam for serveware which is not eco-friendly.

Just stopped in this spot after the White Sox game and we were blown away. We were simply looking for something, anything to soak up the booze and  oy were we surprised!!!! The chicken was so tender and crispy on the outside. The heat was just right too!!!! You get a sweet heat from the chicken unlike anything I've ever tasted before. I will never look at fried chicken the same
The Spicy Chicken Sandwich was delicious! I ordered a side of ranch and the hot level. I will be doing extra hot next time.
Very good! Ordered the 4 piece chicken tender and it was delicious! A little more expensive but for comfort food definitely well worth it. Will be returning soon for sure!
Great spot.  Chicken was fantastic.
Best Nashville style fried chicken in Bridgeport!
I had the big boss sandwich....it was the BOMB!
Fantastic tasting but the chicken was clearly steroid huge.

My wife and I stopped by this afternoon for a quick lunch. We ordered a Half Bird(half medium spicy and half mild) and a Big Boss sandwich(medium spicy) with two fountain drinks. I barely finished the sandwich on my own and needed to skip dinner lol. The chicken tasted so good and medium spicy is spicier than most high spicy I have tried. The place is very close to the Halsted Orange Line train station.
Below average chicken quality for being a place dedicated to chicken.
Food was great! The spicy ness of the chicken was very enjoyable.  Definitely coming back.
The chicken sandwich is a must try. The wait time is long so order ahead!

Upon walking up to this place, I had to question whether or not it was open to the public. If the open sign wasn't there, I wouldn't have known. Going inside, the area was small, cozy, if you may. If there wasn't people sitting down and eating, I'd be suspect of the place being legit. I waited for a while before someone helped us at the counter. The lady was rude. Non apologetic for having us wait for such a long time, begins with, "What do you want to order?". Ok. I ordered the 1 of the 2 spicy lunchbox. Btw, they don't serve free water, you'd have to purchase a bottle. Sat down, waited for 20 mins. Not too long after I sat, a couple of customer waited by the counter. The whole time, the lady was never to be seen. Until, of course, 20 mins later, she comes out with our food and then rudely took the 2 customers order. No apologies, again. I mean, c'mon, what is up with the service here? Does she work in the front and the back? Anyways, the food was bland. Spicy, though. Too bad that's all it was. I don't believe I will go back to even try the fried chicken. Maybe delivery would've been better because then you won't have to witness how bad the service was.
Best spicy fried chicken sandwich! Big sandwich and the sauces are delicious (very hot).

If you ever want to try the most delicious moist crunchy in every bite chicken sandwich the come to this place! I have been seeing this place in my FB feed and once I was nearby I popped in to have lunch. OMG!!!! I am in chicken sandwich heaven.  I got the sandwich flavor in HOT. Let me tell you just enough heat for me. I don't think I could've gone hotter. Every bite was crunchy until the end. The combination of heat with creamy crunchy coleslaw was the most amazing combination I have ever tasted. I am so coming here again I want to be hungry again RIGHT NOW to have another sandwich. $8 is a great price for this delight.  The Mac-n-Cheese was a great addition.  Creamy cheesy with what looked like a touch of pepper was the coup de gras!  All I can say is come try it for yourself.  If you have an open mind for flavor you will love this place. Not much to look at as a restaurant but who cares, you come to eat, not relax! Eat away,  thank me later! They didn't get 5 stars because they want you to BUY water instead of just giving you a cup of water. I certainly didn'tike that.
(Translated by Google) Visit this rrestauranted It is a very pleasant experience  (Original) Visitar este rrestauranted Es una experiencia muy agradable

Incredibly tasty and flavorful food. If you like hot chicken, do not, I repeat, did not pass up the opportunity to enjoy Big Boss. Your taste buds will never forget the experience. Even the iced tea had more flavor than any iced tea I've ever enjoyed.
Great fried chicken joint. Will return.
Great food

This place was recommended by a friend as “the best fried chicken I’ve ever had.”  Entering from the outside, you’re not sure what to make of it. Lots of graffiti, and a huge chicken art. Not what one typically thinks for the Asian-styled chicken my friend raved about.  Inside it is extremely clean. 5/5 passes the “would I take my Asian mom there”  We got two chicken sandwiches and a half chicken: mild, medium and hot.  The chicken sandwiches were really good! Fresh chicken, fully seasoned, with coleslaw that pairs well. It maintains its juiciness while keeping the breading crisp. If anything, it might be almost too intense.  The half chicken flavoring was intense, while the breading maintained its tenderness. Chicken was good, “not extremely special,” but paired well with the breading. They probably brine the chicken, which makes it taste juicier than others.  Bonus: Passion Fruit Green Tea is a 10/10.  Overall, I would go again. 10/10. I don’t have enough experience with fried chicken as my friend, but this is definitely up there and a must try.
Definitely get the Big Boss sandwich 👌

Absolutely LOVE this place, I highly recommend the spicy chicken sandwich and their curry fries ( order medium spicy because it’s already spicy 🌶). The Cashier Is very welcoming and hospitable. Try this place, you won’t be disappointed!

Delicious fried chicken! Unique flavor but very tasty! Big portion for a good price. Their fruit tea is pretty good too and refreshing. They also have salad and soup in their menu for the healthier selection.

The place was an absolute let down. I read the reviews from the online Chicago rags that heralded this place as a next level Harold’s . The reviews on here made it seem like a flavorful mix  of unique flavors. Maybe a little Leons mixed with an Asian flair but NO all we got was steaming hot pieces of poultry  that were soggy. If you’re frying chicken at 400 degrees how does it come out greasy and soggy? We ordered half mild and half medium whole chicken (tray A). There was no hint of any flavors, no uniqueness, no Asian or “California” fusion. The mild was just heat. That’s it. Heat. I’ve eaten Leon’s hot links, I’ve eaten spicy hot Harold’s gizzards and they had more complexity than Big Boss’s chicken. Oh by the way the only difference between the mild and medium chicken was addition of smoked paprika. Wow, I put smoked paprika to add a layer of flavor to my dishes but I sure don’t use it as a main ingredient. Frankly I’m angry that I got taken for $36.00 for way below sub par food. I took the food home out of principal and threw it away. While on my walk home I wished a MF’r would’ve tried to mug me so I could take out my frustration of wasting my time and money at Big Boss Spicy Fried Chicken on them. Plus I’ll leave you with this, how is the flesh of the chicken searing hot but the main joint of the wing cold? Frying half frozen pieces?

We just came back from Nashville not long ago and we had been craving for fried chicken. If you’ve been to Nashville, one of the food you must try is the fried chicken. Anyway, we saw this restaurant has quite good reviews and decided to come and try. We ordered the chicken sandwich and the wings. The chicken sandwich was medium spicy, but it was already very spicy for my husband. We usually have quite spicy food, but medium level was already very spicy for my husband so it means it’s VERY spicy. The chicken wings were mild, and it already had some kicks. I enjoyed this one better. The fried chickens were very tasty, not just the batter only but also the meats. The only thing I didn’t like was the chicken wings were so big, each wing looked like a turkey leg. I wish they were smaller.  Overall: Menu: 4stars Service: 5stars Food: 4stars Price: $
Had the chicken sandwich today, extra hot, so freaking delicious!! Will definitely be coming here again!
I thought it was over priced but once I opened the box  it was worth it.  Very spicy witch is what I like.  However they could throw in some fries or something with the entrees.
Super authentic Spicy fried chicken. You must give it a shot!
Best Chicken Sandwich
Delicious and tender spicy fried chicken! I’m sensitive to heat so I tried the mild, which is still pretty spicy, but not unbearable. My favorite are the cheese puffs.

User beware. Their "medium spicy" chicken sandwich is REALLY spicy. I felt like my stomach lining was degenerating. But... the less spicy chicken... is no sauce chicken. WHY? Oddly, the medium wings and chicken tenders were sensibly spicy (but still pretty spicy).
Really good fried chicken. Spicy, crisp and JUICY! To make it simple, definitely better than Popeyes, KFC and other chains.
Very spicy, one suggestion maybe a bit crispier for the breading
Seriously good hot fried chicken. Best thing is it wasn't all mouth torturing heat; it had actual discernable flavor. The service through grubhub was also fast. Look forward to eating in soon.

Best hot chicken I have ever tried. One of the best meal in chi town so far. Must try their “must try chicken sandwich”.  If you think you can handle really spicy food, go for medium spicy - it will be really hot.
The house  sandwiches is the best . Wings are very juicy but not the best .
Juicy Fried chicken. Overall is good, spicy is as expected. The order experience could be better, and the waiting time is a little long. Improve this, would be very good
Chicken is fire! Large pieces, crispy, and spicy. I recommend getting it with the sauce on the side.

Wow! So happy that they’re open! Spicy fried chicken served several ways and at five different spice levels. They have sides, too; the macaroni and cheese is delicious and creamy.  The batter/fry itself, WITHOUT SAUCE, is spicy (like Tobasco level) and then things get hotter with each sauce you add. REALLY SPICY. FEEL THE BURN, got it? If you’re into spicy fried chicken, then this is the place for you.

I moved from Nashville, TN to Chicago and was searching for best fried chicken places here that can replace the best fried chicken places I had in Nashville, I tried many in Chicago but nothing comes first than this place. Ultimate spicy fried chicken in Chicago
Great spot, Spot on season, Good price for portion. 🔥
Spicy chicken that isn't just hot. So yummy!
Have the sandwich!
One of the Best Spicy Friend Chicken place in Chicago. This restaurant is nearby my house I'm officially a regular here now.

I saw this restaurant come up on Uber eats and I decided to give it a shot! I didn’t know what to expect, so I just ordered some tenders, fries, and Mac & Cheese. Everything was at a great price... the chicken was only about $9 for 4 tenders.  When I opened the box, I was SHOCKED by how large the portions were. On top of that, the chicken is much spicier than you think! I ordered just the medium spice and was expecting some typical buffalo wings... but it had much more flavor than that! If you really like spicy food, I think you might like the hotter flavors!!  I will DEFINITELY be ordering again sometime soon!!
